cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with object recognition and leverages visual representations. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a new approach to Zero-Shot Learning using semantic representations. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the proposed approach involves modeling the conditional likelihood of an object to appear in a given context. 
4. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is relevant as the paper deals with semantic representations and their use in object recognition. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) is relevant as the experiments are conducted on the Visual Genome dataset, which is a multimedia dataset containing images and their associated textual descriptions.
